An engineering society sponsors a resume review table near the stage, and as students use kiosks to upload their resumes to the fair database, interview sign-up sheets fill with names as the day winds down. Some students rehearse elevator pitches quietly against the wall. Announcement chimes signal the final hour of the fair, and a post-event survey link flashes on monitors near the exit. Meanwhile, friends decompress on the quad, comparing which companies responded warmly. An aroma of coffee and catered snacks spreads from the lounge.

International students queued for advice on visa sponsorship requirements. A resume review table sponsored by the engineering society was located near the stage, while a whiteboard listed employers scheduling same-day interviews. Alumni volunteers shared quick pep talks near the coffee station, and students used tablets at kiosks to upload resumes to the fair database. Announcement chimes signaled the final hour of the fair, prompting students to exit with tote bags and stacks of business cards. Interview sign-up sheets filled with names as the day wound down, while friends decompressed on the quad, comparing which companies responded warmly. Camera crews from the university media team captured interviews, as finance firms offered QR codes for immediate internship applications, healthcare providers showcased community outreach photos, and tech companies displayed demo screens showing their latest apps. Additionally, a startup founder invited students to a lunchtime pitch session, while a post-event survey link flashed on the monitors near the exit.
